%% DALP custody integration flow.
%% Shows how DALP integrates with custody providers (Fireblocks, DFNS, HSM).
%% Use in custody, key management, security architecture, and operational controls sections.
%% Covers: key generation, transaction signing with maker-checker, balance reconciliation, custody attestation.
%%{init: {
  "theme": "base",
  "themeVariables": {"fontFamily": "Figtree, Inter, Arial, sans-serif", "fontSize": "15px", "textColor": "#1A1A2E", "lineColor": "#6B7280", "background": "#FFFFFF"},
  "sequence": {"mirrorActors": false, "showSequenceNumbers": false, "diagramMarginX": 40, "diagramMarginY": 20, "messageMargin": 28, "boxMargin": 12, "actorMargin": 40, "width": 170, "height": 64},
  "securityLevel": "loose"
}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant OP as Operator<br/>(Asset Console)
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant KG as Key Guardian
    participant TS as Transaction Signer
    participant HSM as HSM / KMS
    participant CUST as Custody Provider<br/>(Fireblocks / DFNS)
    participant BC as Blockchain

    Note over OP,BC: Key Generation Flow

    OP->>EE: Request new signing key
    EE->>KG: Initiate key generation
    KG->>HSM: Generate key pair (HSM policy check)
    HSM-->>KG: Public key + key reference
    KG->>CUST: Register vault / wallet
    CUST-->>KG: Vault ID + address
    KG-->>EE: Key provisioned
    EE-->>OP: Wallet ready

    Note over OP,BC: Transaction Signing Flow (Maker-Checker)

    OP->>EE: Submit transaction request
    EE->>KG: Request signing approval
    KG->>KG: Validate RBAC + policy rules
    KG->>OP: Maker-checker: await second approver

    alt Approved by second operator
        OP->>KG: Second approval granted
        KG->>TS: Authorize signing
        TS->>HSM: Sign transaction payload
        HSM-->>TS: Signed transaction
        TS->>CUST: Co-sign (if multi-sig policy)
        CUST-->>TS: Co-signature
        TS->>BC: Broadcast signed transaction
        BC-->>TS: Transaction hash + receipt
        TS-->>EE: Execution confirmed
        EE-->>OP: Transaction success
    else Rejected or timeout
        KG-->>EE: Signing denied
        EE-->>OP: Transaction rejected
    end

    Note over OP,BC: Balance Reconciliation (Scheduled)

    EE->>CUST: Query custody balances
    CUST-->>EE: Custody balance report
    EE->>BC: Query on-chain balances
    BC-->>EE: On-chain balance state
    EE->>EE: Compare and flag discrepancies
    EE-->>OP: Reconciliation report

    Note over CUST: [CLIENT: Insert specific custody provider and policy configuration here]
